Steps per revolution is how many steps it takes to turn the stepper one
 revolution.
\layout Standard

Micro steps is how many steps the drive needs to move the stepper one step.
\layout Standard

Motor & Leadscrew Teeth is if you have some reduction between the motor
 and the leadscrew.
 If not set these to 1.
\layout Standard

Leadscrew pitch is how many turns it takes to move your table one user unit.
 If your setting up in inches then it is turns per inch.
 If your setting up in millimeters then how many turns per millimeter.
 
